    "what_description": "Thelypteris levyi is a species of fern in the family Aspleniaceae. It is characterized by its bipinnate fronds, 30-60 cm long, with pinnae 2-3 cm wide and 5-7 pairs of pinnules. The plant's rhizome is erect and scaly, while its stipe is yellowish-brown and glabrous. Thelypteris levyi is native to Mexico, and its habitats include tropical and subtropical forests. The species is part of the genus Thelypteris, which consists of about 300 species of ferns.",
