    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Thelypteris levyi are its antioxidant activity, which is attributed to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic acids that scavenge free radicals and protect against oxidative stress. The plant's anti-inflammatory property is due to the saponins and terpenoids that inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory cytokines and enzymes, reducing inflammation and pain. Additionally, its antimicrobial property is attributed to the volatile oils and glycosides that exhibit antibacterial and antifungal activities, preventing infections and promoting wound healing. Thelypteris levyi also exhibits hepatoprotective activity, thanks to the flavonoids and phenolic acids that protect the liver from oxidative damage and inflammation, and its antiviral activity is due to the saponins and terpenoids that inhibit the replication of viral particles. The bioactive compounds present in Thelypteris levyi contribute to its therapeutic potential, making it a valuable resource for the development of new medicines.",
